<br />
     </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This deck is essentially thought to arrive, not to kill, but sometimes it does.<br />
<br><br />
For this purpose, you can bid lots of burdens to start. The typical shire cards will alow you to run though the first sites (if you don&#39;t have an awful hand) and the nazgûl can stop your opponent in the beginning. &#39;Cause of the few rares in the deck, I didn&#39;t include promises, though they would make it stronger. <br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
The strategy is very simple: hobbit farmer and green hill country, talent for not being seen and bill the pony will give little pool to your opponent. Hobbit party guest, farmer maggot, gaffer and frodo will protect you from bowmen decks. Filibert protects you from Nazgûl, and Bilbo can save your life removing a goblin swarms from play. Thor&#39;s map is there to avoid Anduin Confluence (it discards every ally). I also have played this including Boromir, son of Denethor and Boromir&#39;s cloak to avoid Saruman snows and give extra help to the hobbits, but it makes the deck bigger.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
The shadow side tries to exert with under the watching eye and wound your opponent when possible, and prevents him/her from healing with Black Breath. Relentless charge gives more than a surprise to the typical archer deck, and fear could make so much damage to a hobbit deck similar, with gaffer, maggot, party guest and all that stuff.<br />
<br><br />
<br />
<br><br />
This deck was very good until flaming brands appeared, but it still works very well, and the hobbits can run and suffer a lot before dying. <br />
<br><br />
